How to install the server:
1) install node.js with npm
2) In windows socket.io depends on node-gyp which depends on several other stuff:
see https://github.com/TooTallNate/node-gyp for the requirements before the installation
(i.e. install Visual Studio Express 2010 and 2012 and Windows SDK 7.1)
3) open a terminal and change to the directory ../serenity/src/server
4) execute the command "npm install"

How to start the server:
1) open a terminal and change to the directory ../serenity/src/server
2) execute "node server.js"